8","24 August 1307":"24 August 1307","1296":"1296","1350":"1350","1372":"1372","1273":"1273","1307":"1307","Elderslie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Elderslie, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland","Eldeslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayr Cemetery, Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Elderslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Elderslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland","London, England":"London, England, United Kingdom","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Almour","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Andre, Armand, Dominique, Ermite, Evens, Gabrielle, Ghislaine, Jacques, Marcel, Marie Nicole, Maryse, Mireille.","French: from Old French <i>l'amour</i> ‘(the) friendship, bond’, used as a nickname for a kindly individual. In France, this surname is most common in Brittany and Pas-de-Calais.","Haitian: from the male personal name or nickname <i>L'Amour</i>, which has the same meaning as 1 above. This surname is also found in the Dominican Republic."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Mary Almour was born in 1278, in Elderslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland. She married Sir John Wallace - Laird of Elderslie in 1296, in Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1372, in Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland, at the age of 94, and was buried in Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1278–1372":"1278–1372","1273–1307":"1273–1307","1298–1350":"1298–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1307–1377":"1307–1377","1305":"1305","about 1305":"umbes 1305","1278":"1278","1377":"1377","1298":"1298","24 August 1307":"24. august 1307","1296":"1296","1350":"1350","1372":"1372","1273":"1273","1307":"1307","Elderslie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Elderslie, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland","Eldeslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayr Cemetery, Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Elderslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Elderslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland","London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1278–1372":"1278–1372","1273–1307":"1273–1307","1298–1350":"1298–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1307–1377":"1307–1377","1305":"1305","about 1305":"noin 1305","1278":"1278","1377":"1377","1298":"1298","24 August 1307":"24. elokuuta 1307","1296":"1296","1350":"1350","1372":"1372","1273":"1273","1307":"1307","Elderslie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Elderslie, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland","Eldeslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayr Cemetery, Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Elderslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Elderslie, Renfrewshire, Scotland","London, England":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1278–1372":"1278–1372","1273–1307":"1273–1307","1298–1350":"1298–1350","1305–Male":"1305–Décédé","1307–1377":"1307–1377","1305":"1305","about 1305":"environ 1305","1278":"1278","1377":"1377","1298":"1298","24 August 1307":"24 août 1307","1296":"1296","1350":"1350","1372":"1372","1273":"1273","1307":"1307","Elderslie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Elders